Roles and Responsibilities as Linux / System (Admin, Engineer, Support, Consultant, Developer)
 
User and Permission Management
Manage user accounts, permissions, and access controls.
Implement security measures to safeguard systems and data.
Server Security through Discretionary and SELinux policies, implementing firewall, allow and disallow port access.
 
Installation and Package Management
Install, configure, and maintain Linux operating systems (e.g., CentOS, Ubuntu, Red Hat) - (Network Boot)
Set up and maintain web servers (e.g., Apache, Nginx) and database servers (e.g., MariaDB, PostgreSQL).
Perform routine system updates and patches.
Configure and manage virtualization environments (e.g., VMware, KVM).
Planned and executed packages and updates installations necessary for optimal system performance.
 
Monitoring
Monitor system performance and troubleshoot issues proactively.
Monitoring and resolving high CPU load and memory load related issues.
Monitor network traffic and identify potential vulnerabilities.
Monitor server resources and optimize performance.
 
Backup and Schedule
Scheduling backups and log rotations using cron service.
Backup and restore critical data and applications.
Created new backup system for site's database servers, allowing data archives to be stored on remote server.
Develop scripts (e.g., Bash, Python) to automate routine tasks and system administration processes.
 
Troubleshooting
Configure and troubleshoot network interfaces and protocols.
Provide temporary root access to local users
Configuration of remote access utilities such as SSH with password less authentication
Remote administration and monitoring of Servers using tools like SSH, FTP, TELNET, SCP & Manage installed services.
Kernel patching; root password recovery; solving grub issue
 
Manage Services
Creating and managing partitions and volumes
Configuration of NAS storage using NFS and samba; Sharing partitions using ISCSI storage and RAID storage.
Configure LAMP, Wordpress, Cpanel, Tomcat Platforms
 
Other Tools
Utilize configuration management tools Ansible for automated deployment and configuration management.
Install and Configure Jenkins Server on client environment
Created kubernetes cluster using kubeadm
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to support various IT projects and initiatives.
Document system configurations, procedures, and troubleshooting steps.
Provide technical support and guidance to team members and end-users
 
Roles and Responsibilities as AWS / Cloud (Admin, Engineer, Support, Consultant, Developer)
 
Cloud Infrastructure Management
Design, implement, and maintain scalable and secure cloud infrastructures
Monitor and manage cloud services to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
Create infrastructure with best practices using AWS Stack VPC, EC2, RDS, Route53, CloudFront, s3, IAM, and Cloudwatch
 
Deployment and Migration
Migrate existing applications and data to the cloud while ensuring minimal downtime and high availability.
Optimize cloud infrastructure for cost-efficiency and performance. Using s3 lifecycle, instance purchasing options, etc.
 
Security and Compliance
Ensure the security of cloud systems by implementing best practices in identity and access management (IAM), encryption, and network security.
Maintain compliance with organizational and regulatory requirements like GDPR, HIPAA, etc.
 
Deployment and Automation 
Build and manage CI/CD pipelines for seamless application deployment across cloud environments.
Automate routine tasks like provisioning, configuration, and scaling using tools like Ansible, Jenkins, or GitLab CI/CD.
Enable deployment automation for multi-cloud or hybrid cloud setups.
 
Troubleshooting and Problem Resolution
Identify and resolve issues related to cloud infrastructure, networking, and application deployment.
Collaborate with development and IT teams to troubleshoot performance bottlenecks or failures.
 
Automation and Scripting
Develop automation scripts and tools to improve operational efficiency and reduce manual tasks.
Create CI/CD pipelines for continuous integration and delivery of applications.
 
Collaboration with Teams
Work closely with DevOps teams to integrate cloud solutions into the software development lifecycle.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to align cloud strategies with organizational goals.
 
Monitoring and Optimization
Set up and manage monitoring tools to track usage, performance, and costs
Regularly review cloud spending and make recommendations to optimize costs.
 
Backup and Disaster Recovery
Develop and implement backup strategies to ensure data integrity and availability.
 
 
Research and Development
Stay updated on the latest cloud technologies and services.
Recommend new tools or approaches to improve cloud-based processes and infrastructure.
 
Documentation
Create and maintain technical documentation, including cloud architecture diagrams, configurations, and standard operating procedures (SOPs).
 
Roles and Responsibilities as DevOps (Admin, Engineer, Support, Consultant, Developer)
 
CI/CD Pipeline Development
Design, implement, and maintain Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) pipelines.
Automate build, test, and deployment processes to enhance efficiency.
 
Collaboration Between Teams
Act as a bridge between development, QA, and IT operations teams.
Ensure smooth communication and collaboration to align development and operations objectives.
 
Infrastructure Management
Deploy, configure, and manage servers and cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, GCP, etc.).
Use Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools like Terraform, Ansible, or CloudFormation for automated provisioning.
 
Monitoring and Logging
Set up monitoring tools (e.g., Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, ELK Stack) to track system performance and application health.
Analyze logs to identify and troubleshoot issues proactively.
 
Automation and Scripting
Automate repetitive tasks, including infrastructure setup, application deployment, and scaling.
Write scripts in languages like Bash, Python, or PowerShell for custom automation needs.
 
Security and Compliance
Implement security measures such as role-based access control, encryption, and vulnerability assessments.
Ensure compliance with industry standards like ISO, GDPR, or SOC2.
 
Configuration Management
Manage application configurations using tool Ansible
Ensure consistency across development, staging, and production environments.
 
Containerization and Orchestration
Work with containerization technologies like Docker to package applications.
Use orchestration tool Kubernetes to manage containerized applications and services.
 
Performance Optimization
Identify performance bottlenecks and optimize system resources.
Improve scalability and fault tolerance of applications and infrastructure.
 
Disaster Recovery and Backups
Create and manage backup strategies for critical systems and data.
Develop disaster recovery plans to minimize downtime and data loss.
            vcc
Incident Management
Act as the first point of contact for incidents related to system performance or availability.
Document incident resolution steps to prevent recurrence.
 
Process Improvement
Continuously evaluate and refine DevOps processes for better productivity and agility.
Research and implement new tools and practices to enhance workflows.
 
